BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..subtitle: Titan Vanguard
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..name: Commander Zavala
BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: The resolute Commander Zavala advises Guardians on all Vanguard-related activities.

interactions.flavorLineOne: Zavala thanks you for the thoughtful gift, and begins squeezing it immediately. Forcefully.

"When you achieve the success seen here today, it's not just a personal victory. It's a victory for us all. You ensure that the enemy knows we give no quarter."

Zavala offers a small nod of approval. "Take this and keep reminding them."

"Shock tactics are an important tool for the Vanguard," Zavala says. "The aural and optical devastation of a large ordnance provides a significant tactical advantage and wreaks havoc on enemy morale. Further, while I'm glad to have the comms channels free of such bombast…"

A hint of a smile flashes across his face.

"…even I'll admit the experience is satisfying. Take this, Guardian, and make sure they get your message."

No need to waver, Guardian. The Vanguard stands behind you every step of the way.

The Light is our strength. The Darkness will never take that from us. 

Fight on.

headerDisplayProperties.description: Speak with Zavala about the emerging Vex crisis on the Moon.
headerDisplayProperties.name: The Vex Offensive

interactions.flavorLineOne: Never a dull moment for the Vanguard. While Zavala orchestrates regular operations across the system and directs the fight to keep our hold on the Moon, he trusts you and Ikora to tackle the Vex crisis head-on.

"The Festival of the Lost is a City-wide tradition," Zavala says. "Guardians see death differently than others do, but we all know loss. And that brings us together."

He smiles. "As does celebration. We remember the dead and celebrate the living, so enjoy yourself, Guardian."

headerDisplayProperties.description: Commander Zavala has heard of your success in saving Saint-14 from the Infinite Forest and wishes to thank you. Visit him in the Tower Courtyard.
headerDisplayProperties.name: Zavala

interactions.flavorLineOne: Zavala is amazed by your continuing ability to do the impossible. On behalf of the City, he thanks you for saving Saint-14. He also asks that you help Saint-14 adjust to his new life in the Tower however you can. He expects his return to the City will be a little overwhelming.

Zavala nods respectfully as you approach. His Ghost transmats a Grenade Launcher into his hands.

"This is the Wendigo, so-named for its monstrous hunger. Carry it with honor."

The City has been liberated, but threats to our survival remain. Zavala has authorized the Nightfall protocol to dispatch elite Guardian fireteams for surgical strikes against the greatest of these threats. 

Each week, assemble your fireteam and complete the Nightfall strike to earn valuable rewards.
Zavala congratulates you on your performance in strikes—and offers a reward fit for such a heroic effort.

"Welcome back, Guardian. Your fight against the enemies at our gates has only just begun."

Return to Commander Zavala to acquire bounties, gear, and other rewards related to strike activities.

With a quiet kind of ceremony, Zavala presents you with your reward: a new Oxygen SR3.

"Carry it proudly," he tells you.
Zavala congratulates you on your dedication to fighting the biggest threats to humanity, and he gives you a reward worthy of your heroism.
Zavala recognizes your devotion to completing Vanguard bounties and rewards you with a weapon worthy of that hard work.

Zavala nods approvingly as you approach.

"Excellent work, Guardian. Even smaller tasks play a big part in the Vanguard's operations. Your diligence sets a strong example for us all."
Zavala's expression is unreadable as he accepts the cookies, but he nods in recognition of the thoughtful gift.

"Welcome to the Tower, Guardian. I am Commander Zavala. I, and every citizen of the Last City, need your help."

Commander Zavala is the leader of the Vanguard. He offers bounties, quests, and special rewards for challenges in strike activities.

Hover over the quest icon below and select it with .


ACQUIRE QUEST
You got the revenge you wanted, but Commander Zavala reminds you of what you risked to do so. Uldren's death will have consequences. Of that Zavala is sure.
Zavala doesn't have the luxury of revenge. He has the City to think of. He won't give you his blessing as you head to the Tangled Shore in mission "High Plains Blues."

"Guardian… To hold off oblivion, we must be vigilant against the enemies who threaten our existence."

Vanguard bounties offer focused objectives for Guardians to complete while playing strike activities.

Select Vanguard bounties from Commander Zavala. Complete their objectives, then claim your completed bounties to gain XP and rewards.

Zavala carries upon his shoulders the burden of guilt for the loss of the City. The truth is this was a wake-up call for all of humanity. It's time to shore up our defenses and take the fight to our enemies. 

Report back to Zavala for Nightfall and strike activities.

Zavala will never trust Rasputin, but for now he'll put his faith in Ana Bray. The future may be uncertain, but he is reassured knowing he has a Guardian he can trust. You have earned his praise by destroying Xol and saving Mars.

"You have stood against every foe and driven them to break. A commendable effort, Guardian. One that does not go unnoticed.

"I assume you've heard the people recounting your deeds throughout the City? You command their respect, and hold their hope. They look to you as the first who will stand against the coming tide. I know you will not fail them. Carry on." —Commander Zavala

"Stolen? No one outside of the Vanguard should have access to the vault, let alone revoke our access. If this is a breach, we will need to boost security measures considerably. While we were looking up to the sky, someone snuck in right under our noses."

Zavala rubs his chin, pensively.

"I want answers and I want that weapon recovered. I know of some BrayTech equipment that can help us track it down. Go see Ana on Mars."

Commander Zavala straightens his stance and meets your eyes directly. "I've heard of your… adventures." His shoulders relax. "Impeccable work, Guardian. You've transcended our expectations yet again."

Zavala buries a prideful smile. "However, there is always more work to be done. Remain on the fireteam, and remain vigilant. Carry on."
Ana believes Rasputin can help destroy the Almighty before it hits the City. He's reluctant to trust the Warmind, but asks you to go to Mars to speak with Ana.

"Guardian, there's something I'd like you to retrieve from the Vanguard vault. We've been storing certain high-value weapons here since losing our vaults during the Red War. The Cabal seek to destroy us with the Almighty. I want to send them a message, and I have the perfect delivery method. Take this keycard to the vault."

Before you can take the keycard, Zavala pulls it back.

"You'll have to go through my office to access it. I normally do not allow Guardians in there, so I'm trusting you not to disrupt any of my… personal effects. Grab the weapon and come back to me."
Travel to Mars to speak to Ana about Rasputin.
Show Zavala proof of your deeds in the Vanguard war effort.
Your reputation in the Vanguard war effort precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
Complete bounties for XP and undertake quests for valuable gear. Completing strikes grants you tokens, which can be turned in here for packages.
Your reputation in the Crucible precedes you. Take this reward in recognition of your deeds.
Increase your level to claim these rewards.

failureStrings: Source: Complete the "Season 8: First Watch" quest.
Requires completion of the "Honor Bound" pursuit.
Requires completion of the "City Defender" quest.
